# Exploration: od

## Test scope
  490 behavioral groups: 324 unique, 166 shared

  Contexts referenced in exemplars below:
    words_minimal: 1500 English words; input.txt + other.txt
    words_minimal / stdin: piped input via stdin
    words_standard: 1500 English words; files, hidden, subdir, symlink, executable, readonly

## Observed: 18/21 flags
  11 uniquely observable, 7 distinguishable via flag pairs
  3 error-only (flag recognized but no successful output observed)
  3 behavioral aliases (different flags, identical behavior)
  robustness: 20 verified in all contexts, 0 in most, 0 context-dependent

Aliases: -A = --address-radix, -N = --read-bytes, -j = --skip-bytes, -t = --format, -v = --output-duplicates

## Unique behavior (observable when tested alone)
  --endian  # swap input bytes according the specified order
    tested: "--endian=big" "input.txt" "other.txt" in words_minimal
    | flag adds 663 lines: 0000000 060541 071144 073141 071153 005141 061142 071145 073151, 0000020 060564 064557 067012 060542 067565 072012 060542 071564, 0000040 071141 061564 005141 061543 062560 072012 060543 061545, 0000060 070164 062544 005141 061543 062560 072151 067147 005141, 0000100 061543 062563 071412 060543 061557 066555 067544 060564
